<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Former Liverpool striker Luis Suarez will complete a sensational move to Atletico Madrid after they agreed a fee with Barcelona.</p>

<p>Barca announced that they had agreed a deal which would see the Catalan club receive six million euros (£5.5m).</p>

<p>Suarez joined Barca in 2014 and helped the club win four LaLiga titles, four Copa del Reys and the Champions League in 2015.</p>

<p>Atletico confirmed via their official website that Suarez will join them subject to him passing a medical and his contract being formalised.</p>

<p>Barcelona, meanwhile, thanked Suarez for his significant contribution to the club.</p>

<p>The 33-year-old will have a farewell press conference at the Nou Camp on Thursday afternoon.</p>
